more places than one, at one time. Wherefore to say that the soules of Martyrs, be euery where, is to deny them to be creatures and so make them gods. I doubt not but S. Ieronym if he had quietly considered these absurdities, would haue reuoked them as erroneous and hereticall: but while he rather followed affection, then iudgement, you may see how he was deceaued. Thus seeing we haue noted to you the names of diuerse heretikes, which first preached certeyne articles of your doctrine, and you are not able to name any, which preached any article of our doctrine, but the same was consonant to the Scripture. If you were as ready to performe, as you are to promise, you should recant.
