                                 Iucae 11. &amp; 16.
                               by thine owne hands or appointment, liuing in this world, which is the best, perfectest, and surest meanes that may be: for that purgeth sinnes,
                                 
                                    Dan. 4.
                                 
                                 
                                    Ecc. 3.
                                 
                                 
                                    Tob. 12.
                                 
                               procureth mercy, maketh frendes in the day of dreade, cleanseth beforehand, staieth the soule from death, and lifteth it vp also to life euerlasting.
